description.narrative: COs have strengthened capacity to carry out equity-focused, high-quality Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) programming, using the latest approaches for demand- led sanitation, hygiene promotion and sustainable low-cost water supply., which contributes to Child Health, Sanitation, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Technical expertise and management support provided to all UNICEF work streams for the equitable achievement of the MDGs by 2015, realizing the rights of every child in humanitarian and development contexts
